#: constants/HelpData.ts:74
msgid "After completing the last working set of an exercise, a feedback sheet slides up with two questions. The first asks how the effort felt: Easy (you could have done more), About right, Hard (near your limit), or Couldn't finish all sets. The second asks about pain: No pain, Minor discomfort, or Pain or form issues. If you answer Easy, a third question appears asking whether you want to push harder next time. This lets you deliberately hold the current load even when a session felt light, so the engine respects your intent. If you answer Pain, an optional text field lets you note where you felt it for your own reference. Discomfort is tracked across sessions: one report keeps the load steady, and a second consecutive report adds a note suggesting a form check. The sheet can be dismissed without answering if you prefer not to log feedback for that exercise in that session. Reps-only exercises without a rep range, such as a set with a fixed rep count like 10, are skipped automatically since there is no room to progress within the range."
msgstr "After completing the last working set of an exercise, a feedback sheet slides up with two questions. The first asks how the effort felt: Easy (you could have done more), About right, Hard (near your limit), or Couldn't finish all sets. The second asks about pain: No pain, Minor discomfort, or Pain or form issues. If you answer Easy, a third question appears asking whether you want to push harder next time. This lets you deliberately hold the current load even when a session felt light, so the engine respects your intent. If you answer Pain, an optional text field lets you note where you felt it for your own reference. Discomfort is tracked across sessions: one report keeps the load steady, and a second consecutive report adds a note suggesting a form check. The sheet can be dismissed without answering if you prefer not to log feedback for that exercise in that session. Reps-only exercises without a rep range, such as a set with a fixed rep count like 10, are skipped automatically since there is no room to progress within the range."

